00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:34.440 align:middle line:10%
You mentioned something
you said unifying physics.

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:35.680 align:middle line:10%
What does that mean?

00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:38.730 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, physics
currently is fragmented.

00:02:38.730 --> 00:02:44.370 align:middle line:10%
You have physics for the
big relativistic equations,

00:02:44.370 --> 00:02:47.670 align:middle line:10%
like very big--

00:02:47.670 --> 00:02:50.640 align:middle line:10%
for very big objects.

00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:55.770 align:middle line:10%
Planets, stars, galaxies,
clusters, superclusters.

00:02:55.770 --> 00:03:00.600 align:middle line:10%
And you have physics for the
small, like quantum physics that

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:05.490 align:middle line:10%
deals with particles
and subatomic particles

00:03:05.490 --> 00:03:09.390 align:middle line:10%
and all kinds of dynamics
that are occurring

00:03:09.390 --> 00:03:11.320 align:middle line:10%
in the very small world.

00:03:11.320 --> 00:03:14.490 align:middle line:10%
And these two
theories don't agree.

00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:18.270 align:middle line:10%
They describe the
universe differently.

00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:22.920 align:middle line:10%
One describes it as a
smooth continuum and--

00:03:22.920 --> 00:03:23.970 align:middle line:10%
cosmologically.

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:30.390 align:middle line:10%
And the other one describes
it as quantized, little bits

00:03:30.390 --> 00:03:33.090 align:middle line:10%
or granular in nature.

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:37.120 align:middle line:10%
And the two formalisms
don't work together.

00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:40.560 align:middle line:10%
And this is something
that Einstein

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:43.020 align:middle line:10%
worked till the end
of his life since he

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:49.545 align:middle line:10%
was involved in the beginning
of both of these theories.

00:03:49.545 --> 00:03:54.300 align:middle line:10%
He felt like there must be a
way to connect them clearly

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:57.760 align:middle line:10%
since big things are
made out of small things.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:01.560 align:middle line:10%
So there must be some kind of
relationship between the two.

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:08.250 align:middle line:10%
And it was kind of startling
to me when I was younger

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:10.920 align:middle line:10%
and I was going to
physics conference

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:12.810 align:middle line:10%
and talking with physicists.

00:04:12.810 --> 00:04:16.800 align:middle line:84%
And I was implying
the importance

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:19.890 align:middle line:84%
of finding a unified
view of physics.

00:04:19.890 --> 00:04:22.980 align:middle line:84%
And at the time,
the prevailing view

00:04:22.980 --> 00:04:25.770 align:middle line:84%
was that it was OK
to have two theories.

00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:27.240 align:middle line:90%
They work just fine.

00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:32.350 align:middle line:84%
And we didn't need
to unify them.

00:04:32.350 --> 00:04:37.530 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it was
clear that there

00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:43.770 align:middle line:84%
must be a solution that
involves the small in the big

00:04:43.770 --> 00:04:46.350 align:middle line:84%
and the big with
the small so that it

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:50.640 align:middle line:84%
would be a continuum or an
understanding of our world

00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:53.400 align:middle line:90%
that's unified.

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:57.480 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I encountered
a lot of resistance

00:04:57.480 --> 00:05:01.420 align:middle line:84%
because there was many
different reasons.

00:05:01.420 --> 00:05:05.640 align:middle line:84%
One of them being if
Einstein couldn't find it,

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:09.120 align:middle line:90%
don't even think about it.

00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:13.760 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, many
physicists admire Einstein.

00:05:13.760 --> 00:05:16.370 align:middle line:90%
And they should.

00:05:16.370 --> 00:05:19.520 align:middle line:90%
He was an excellent scientist.

00:05:19.520 --> 00:05:24.360 align:middle line:84%
However, Einstein didn't
have the tools we have today.

00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:27.050 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have the
data we have today.

00:05:27.050 --> 00:05:29.250 align:middle line:90%
We live in a different world.

00:05:29.250 --> 00:05:32.120 align:middle line:84%
It's a world in which
we've observed black holes.

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:34.760 align:middle line:84%
We've observed all
kinds of phenomenons.

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:37.640 align:middle line:84%
We've done experiments in
laboratories that were not

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:39.680 align:middle line:84%
possible at the
time, and so on that

00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:43.970 align:middle line:84%
has led us to a
place where I felt

00:05:43.970 --> 00:05:46.920 align:middle line:84%
like a unified view of
physics could be found.

00:05:46.920 --> 00:05:50.210 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, I believe
if Einstein was around,

00:05:50.210 --> 00:05:52.580 align:middle line:84%
he would have with
everything that's

00:05:52.580 --> 00:05:58.160 align:middle line:84%
known, because what I found that
unify physics is directly linked

00:05:58.160 --> 00:06:03.170 align:middle line:84%
to some of the predictions of
his own theory, which namely

00:06:03.170 --> 00:06:06.550 align:middle line:90%
black holes and singularities.

00:06:06.550 --> 00:06:10.600 align:middle line:84%
>> So I understand, since
we're on the topic of Einstein,

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:14.410 align:middle line:84%
that there was something that he
realized there was this mistake

00:06:14.410 --> 00:06:16.090 align:middle line:90%
that he made.

00:06:16.090 --> 00:06:17.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:20.980 align:middle line:84%
There was a very
important inflection point

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:25.000 align:middle line:84%
in Einstein's
discoveries that was

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:27.760 align:middle line:90%
missed by historians generally.

00:06:27.760 --> 00:06:33.700 align:middle line:10%
And that is that early on,
some of the experiments that

00:06:33.700 --> 00:06:36.610 align:middle line:10%
were done and the
result of his theory

00:06:36.610 --> 00:06:42.640 align:middle line:10%
was interpreted in such a way
that space time, as he describes

00:06:42.640 --> 00:06:46.870 align:middle line:10%
space and time being this fabric
that could bend to produce

00:06:46.870 --> 00:06:55.150 align:middle line:10%
gravity, was interpreted
as only an analytical tool

00:06:55.150 --> 00:06:58.750 align:middle line:10%
to describe reality,
meaning that it

00:06:58.750 --> 00:07:00.850 align:middle line:10%
was a mathematical model.

00:07:00.850 --> 00:07:04.750 align:middle line:10%
And it had no physicality,
reality to it.

00:07:04.750 --> 00:07:08.460 align:middle line:90%


00:07:08.460 --> 00:07:12.520 align:middle line:10%
And the result was
that there was no need

00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:20.320 align:middle line:10%
anymore to have this
fluid dynamic space that

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:22.510 align:middle line:10%
used to be called the ether.

00:07:22.510 --> 00:07:25.960 align:middle line:10%
And so the ether,
which was in physics

00:07:25.960 --> 00:07:33.490 align:middle line:10%
at the time, which Maxwell had
used to write the famous Maxwell

00:07:33.490 --> 00:07:35.710 align:middle line:10%
equations for the
electromagnetic field.

00:07:35.710 --> 00:07:38.620 align:middle line:10%
This ether, which
was supposed to be

00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:41.950 align:middle line:10%
prevalent in all
the space and being

00:07:41.950 --> 00:07:45.200 align:middle line:10%
the medium from
which all waves moved

00:07:45.200 --> 00:07:48.250 align:middle line:10%
and all the dynamics
occurred, this ether

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:52.810 align:middle line:10%
was removed and replaced
with a conceptual model

00:07:52.810 --> 00:07:54.250 align:middle line:10%
called spacetime.

00:07:54.250 --> 00:08:00.650 align:middle line:10%
And Einstein went along
with it for over 10 years.

00:08:00.650 --> 00:08:08.020 align:middle line:10%
And then he eventually realized
that relativity required

00:08:08.020 --> 00:08:12.790 align:middle line:10%
an ether, that space be
filled with this energy,

00:08:12.790 --> 00:08:13.690 align:middle line:10%
with this field.

00:08:13.690 --> 00:08:16.870 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.870 --> 00:08:20.500 align:middle line:10%
But by then, it was too late.

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:24.880 align:middle line:10%
Physicists had taken
off with a certain view.

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:28.720 align:middle line:10%
They ignored him when he
tried to put it back in.

00:08:28.720 --> 00:08:33.190 align:middle line:10%
And as well he had some
significant objections

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:36.429 align:middle line:10%
to the way quantum theory
was being developed.

00:08:36.429 --> 00:08:38.890 align:middle line:10%
And that didn't
make him so popular

00:08:38.890 --> 00:08:41.200 align:middle line:10%
as well in the
physics community.

00:08:41.200 --> 00:08:45.380 align:middle line:10%
So the result is that
ether was removed.

00:08:45.380 --> 00:08:49.150 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was
probably one of the biggest

00:08:49.150 --> 00:08:56.560 align:middle line:84%
downfalls to understanding our
universe and the physics of it

00:08:56.560 --> 00:08:58.930 align:middle line:90%
until modern age.

00:08:58.930 --> 00:09:03.650 align:middle line:84%
Now there's physicists that
are starting to realize this.

00:09:03.650 --> 00:09:05.530 align:middle line:84%
One of them is a
Nobel Prize winner

00:09:05.530 --> 00:09:10.810 align:middle line:84%
in physics, Frank Wilczek
which did a conference in 2017

00:09:10.810 --> 00:09:14.860 align:middle line:84%
called the materiality of the
vacuum, where he actually-- it's

00:09:14.860 --> 00:09:20.260 align:middle line:84%
an excellent conference that
you can find on YouTube.

00:09:20.260 --> 00:09:29.800 align:middle line:84%
Where you can see that
the main problem that's

00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:34.750 align:middle line:84%
occurring in physics that is
stopping us from understanding

00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:39.760 align:middle line:84%
the physical world from one
end to the other with one

00:09:39.760 --> 00:09:44.890 align:middle line:84%
fundamental theory is the
result of having removed

00:09:44.890 --> 00:09:50.380 align:middle line:84%
the ether or having removed
vacuum fluctuation, which

00:09:50.380 --> 00:09:54.010 align:middle line:84%
we found, again,
in modern physics,

00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:56.125 align:middle line:84%
but we named them
something else.

00:09:56.125 --> 00:09:58.900 align:middle line:90%


00:09:58.900 --> 00:10:05.620 align:middle line:84%
So really it's been a sinuous
path towards modern physics.

00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:10.440 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, physics has
become fragmented as a result.

00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:11.240 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:10:11.240 --> 00:10:14.660 align:middle line:10%
So can you set us
straight where do you

00:10:14.660 --> 00:10:18.470 align:middle line:10%
find that we really are today?

00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:25.550 align:middle line:10%
>> Today physics is
in-- really in a bind.

00:10:25.550 --> 00:10:32.540 align:middle line:10%
Physicists are looking
feverishly for new physics,

00:10:32.540 --> 00:10:35.720 align:middle line:10%
where the standard
model is stuck.

00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:37.640 align:middle line:84%
There's more and
more experiments

00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:42.020 align:middle line:84%
that's showing that the standard
model has some serious deviation

00:10:42.020 --> 00:10:44.360 align:middle line:90%
from experiments.

00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:49.160 align:middle line:10%
There is problems with the
standard cosmological model.

00:10:49.160 --> 00:10:56.150 align:middle line:10%
At this point in physics, as
well string theory in general

00:10:56.150 --> 00:11:00.120 align:middle line:10%
is thought to have failed
in unifying physics.

00:11:00.120 --> 00:11:06.910 align:middle line:10%
So it's like everybody is
in this moment of floating,

00:11:06.910 --> 00:11:10.300 align:middle line:10%
kind of lost trying
to find something

00:11:10.300 --> 00:11:12.490 align:middle line:10%
to sink their teeth in.

00:11:12.490 --> 00:11:15.640 align:middle line:10%
And it's a very powerful
moment at the same time

00:11:15.640 --> 00:11:19.030 align:middle line:10%
because it's a moment
of opportunity.

00:11:19.030 --> 00:11:22.600 align:middle line:10%
It is in those moments
typically that something

00:11:22.600 --> 00:11:27.940 align:middle line:10%
emerged that completely
revolutionized physics.

00:11:27.940 --> 00:11:33.340 align:middle line:10%
And so I'm fairly excited
because from the physics

00:11:33.340 --> 00:11:35.590 align:middle line:10%
I've written in the last
few months and the paper

00:11:35.590 --> 00:11:43.750 align:middle line:10%
I'm about to release, I've
solved most of these issues,

00:11:43.750 --> 00:11:50.050 align:middle line:10%
and shown a very continuous
theory from this Planck scale,

00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:53.980 align:middle line:10%
from quantum scale all the
way to cosmological scale,

00:11:53.980 --> 00:11:58.370 align:middle line:10%
predicting all of the
scales accurately, very,

00:11:58.370 --> 00:12:00.370 align:middle line:10%
very accurately.

00:12:00.370 --> 00:12:04.750 align:middle line:10%
All the constants, all the
forces with some 12 to 13

00:12:04.750 --> 00:12:08.990 align:middle line:10%
digit accuracy,
which is remarkable.

00:12:08.990 --> 00:12:13.250 align:middle line:10%
And I'm talking
much to experiments,

00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:15.470 align:middle line:10%
not much to other theories.

00:12:15.470 --> 00:12:20.540 align:middle line:10%
So I'm talking very
accurate predictions that

00:12:20.540 --> 00:12:22.520 align:middle line:10%
are confirmed by experiments.

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:26.360 align:middle line:10%
And as a result, we can
have a complete view

00:12:26.360 --> 00:12:33.980 align:middle line:10%
of the physical world, which
has very profound meaning as

00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:38.030 align:middle line:10%
well in our understanding
of ourselves,

00:12:38.030 --> 00:12:41.870 align:middle line:10%
in our understanding
of our environment,

00:12:41.870 --> 00:12:45.980 align:middle line:10%
our relationship to each
other, and understanding

00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:49.020 align:middle line:10%
of our consciousness
in the midst of it.

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:55.460 align:middle line:84%
>> So with that, what are we
learning about the relationship

00:12:55.460 --> 00:12:58.650 align:middle line:84%
with our self, with our
environment with one another?

00:12:58.650 --> 00:13:01.940 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I think one of the
first things that we're learning

00:13:01.940 --> 00:13:10.600 align:middle line:10%
about ourselves from these
equations is that there is no

00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:15.070 align:middle line:10%
such thing as a
materialistic view,

00:13:15.070 --> 00:13:18.280 align:middle line:10%
because in order to have
a materialistic view,

00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:24.740 align:middle line:10%
you'd have to know what
material is, what matter is.

00:13:24.740 --> 00:13:28.300 align:middle line:84%
And when you look closely,
what this equation

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:35.380 align:middle line:84%
tells you is that matter is
actually an entanglement network

00:13:35.380 --> 00:13:39.970 align:middle line:84%
of information, that it
is a flow of information

00:13:39.970 --> 00:13:41.380 align:middle line:90%
through a field.

00:13:41.380 --> 00:13:44.860 align:middle line:90%
There is nothing really there.

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:48.130 align:middle line:84%
There's just a
field, and the field

00:13:48.130 --> 00:13:52.360 align:middle line:84%
organizes itself in little
particles we call matter.

00:13:52.360 --> 00:13:55.900 align:middle line:84%
But when you look
closely, all you can see

00:13:55.900 --> 00:14:00.460 align:middle line:84%
is an electrostatic field that
defines a region of space.

00:14:00.460 --> 00:14:02.260 align:middle line:90%
We call it a particle.

00:14:02.260 --> 00:14:07.000 align:middle line:84%
But there's not like a
thing, like people think

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:09.260 align:middle line:90%
of particles as billiard balls.

00:14:09.260 --> 00:14:11.420 align:middle line:90%
They're not billiard balls.

00:14:11.420 --> 00:14:14.660 align:middle line:90%
They're just fields in space.

00:14:14.660 --> 00:14:17.840 align:middle line:10%
And it's the space that
provides the energy

00:14:17.840 --> 00:14:19.400 align:middle line:10%
to produce the fields.

00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:21.260 align:middle line:90%
And that's what was missed.

00:14:21.260 --> 00:14:25.460 align:middle line:84%
And it was missed because,
as I was saying historically,

00:14:25.460 --> 00:14:28.580 align:middle line:84%
the ether or the
energy of the field

00:14:28.580 --> 00:14:30.870 align:middle line:90%
was removed from the equations.

00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:31.670 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

