00:28:19.370 --> 00:28:24.160 align:middle line:84%
And one of those researchers,
Elizabeth Rauscher, Dr. Rauscher

00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:25.330 align:middle line:90%
was my co-author.

00:28:25.330 --> 00:28:27.730 align:middle line:84%
So I discussed it
at length with her.

00:28:27.730 --> 00:28:30.460 align:middle line:84%
And they were
pulling random people

00:28:30.460 --> 00:28:36.460 align:middle line:84%
like students out of campus
and sticking them in the room

00:28:36.460 --> 00:28:39.970 align:middle line:84%
and asking them to remote view
a place in Russia or whatever.

00:28:39.970 --> 00:28:44.560 align:middle line:84%
And they were getting
incredible results,

00:28:44.560 --> 00:28:52.500 align:middle line:84%
like very significantly
non-trivial statistical results

00:28:52.500 --> 00:28:57.810 align:middle line:84%
showing clearly that people
had non-local access, even

00:28:57.810 --> 00:29:01.560 align:middle line:84%
people that were not
trained in any way,

00:29:01.560 --> 00:29:03.850 align:middle line:84%
they weren't
spiritual in any way.

00:29:03.850 --> 00:29:07.087 align:middle line:10%
They were not-- they were just
a random student they picked off

00:29:07.087 --> 00:29:07.887 align:middle line:10%
the street.

00:29:07.887 --> 00:29:17.700 align:middle line:10%
So we call that
intuition in many ways.

00:29:17.700 --> 00:29:20.790 align:middle line:84%
We call that-- we have
all kinds of names for it.

00:29:20.790 --> 00:29:24.030 align:middle line:84%
Remote healing, remote
viewing, all this stuff,

00:29:24.030 --> 00:29:27.960 align:middle line:90%
remote influencing.

00:29:27.960 --> 00:29:33.120 align:middle line:84%
And these are all evidence
that we are tapped

00:29:33.120 --> 00:29:36.280 align:middle line:90%
into a field of information.

00:29:36.280 --> 00:29:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And that actually creative
capacity of a being

00:29:43.850 --> 00:29:49.070 align:middle line:84%
is actually their capacity
to tap into this field

00:29:49.070 --> 00:29:54.800 align:middle line:84%
and extract information and
come up with something new.

00:29:54.800 --> 00:30:00.560 align:middle line:10%
Like if you look in history and
you read the history of science,

00:30:00.560 --> 00:30:04.130 align:middle line:10%
you will find that most of
the greatest discoveries that

00:30:04.130 --> 00:30:08.360 align:middle line:10%
were made in science
were made by somebody

00:30:08.360 --> 00:30:13.800 align:middle line:10%
that was highly intuitive,
somebody that followed their gut

00:30:13.800 --> 00:30:14.600 align:middle line:10%
feeling.

00:30:14.600 --> 00:30:17.390 align:middle line:10%
I mean, so many of them when
they were asked, How did you

00:30:17.390 --> 00:30:21.050 align:middle line:10%
come up with that? it was so
different than anything else

00:30:21.050 --> 00:30:21.890 align:middle line:10%
that was known.

00:30:21.890 --> 00:30:26.420 align:middle line:10%
And they said-- typically
they say I had a gut feeling.

00:30:26.420 --> 00:30:29.720 align:middle line:10%
I had an intuition that
it may be like that.

00:30:29.720 --> 00:30:33.050 align:middle line:10%
Of course, they
followed the lead.

00:30:33.050 --> 00:30:36.230 align:middle line:10%
Most people might have
the exact same intuition,

00:30:36.230 --> 00:30:41.160 align:middle line:10%
but never actually
do the rigorous work

00:30:41.160 --> 00:30:46.620 align:middle line:10%
that it took to follow
those intuition.

00:30:46.620 --> 00:30:47.910 align:middle line:10%
But some of them did.

00:30:47.910 --> 00:30:51.180 align:middle line:10%
And when they did, they found,
Oh, wow, maybe it's right.

00:30:51.180 --> 00:30:53.250 align:middle line:10%
And then publish.

00:30:53.250 --> 00:30:58.570 align:middle line:10%
I mean, how did Einstein come
up with the relativity of space

00:30:58.570 --> 00:30:59.370 align:middle line:10%
and time?

00:30:59.370 --> 00:31:03.090 align:middle line:10%
I mean, this is not
clearly something

00:31:03.090 --> 00:31:07.620 align:middle line:10%
that's evident to
you on a daily basis.

00:31:07.620 --> 00:31:14.730 align:middle line:10%
And this is what's missing
generally in current physics,

00:31:14.730 --> 00:31:21.330 align:middle line:10%
is that the tendency is to think
that if we render enough math,

00:31:21.330 --> 00:31:25.290 align:middle line:10%
and if we just follow
the math somehow,

00:31:25.290 --> 00:31:28.060 align:middle line:10%
it's going to tell us
how the universe works.

00:31:28.060 --> 00:31:30.630 align:middle line:10%
And that's just not the case.

00:31:30.630 --> 00:31:33.420 align:middle line:10%
All the great
discoveries in physics

00:31:33.420 --> 00:31:40.570 align:middle line:10%
were done by people that
had a model in their head.

00:31:40.570 --> 00:31:48.030 align:middle line:10%
They had-- or in the field
that they had come up with.

00:31:48.030 --> 00:31:49.740 align:middle line:90%
They had an intuition.

00:31:49.740 --> 00:31:51.410 align:middle line:90%
They had a feeling.

00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:54.840 align:middle line:10%
They had reflections--
deep reflections

00:31:54.840 --> 00:31:57.480 align:middle line:10%
about the nature of
reality in the field

00:31:57.480 --> 00:31:58.710 align:middle line:10%
that they were studying.

00:31:58.710 --> 00:32:00.570 align:middle line:10%
They came up with something.

00:32:00.570 --> 00:32:03.270 align:middle line:10%
And then they went
to the mathematics

00:32:03.270 --> 00:32:05.760 align:middle line:10%
to see if it pans out.

00:32:05.760 --> 00:32:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And then mathematics
makes sense.

00:32:10.260 --> 00:32:14.560 align:middle line:84%
And actually, then mathematics
is an excellent tool.

00:32:14.560 --> 00:32:17.490 align:middle line:84%
It's an excellent
language, because it really

00:32:17.490 --> 00:32:20.970 align:middle line:84%
helps your cognitive
mind actually understand.

00:32:20.970 --> 00:32:22.890 align:middle line:90%
And this is really important.

00:32:22.890 --> 00:32:26.580 align:middle line:84%
Because, for instance, the
equations I wrote basically

00:32:26.580 --> 00:32:28.260 align:middle line:90%
tells us we're all one.

00:32:28.260 --> 00:32:34.390 align:middle line:84%
But you know how many people in
the world, how many masters have

00:32:34.390 --> 00:32:38.300 align:middle line:84%
gone throughout the ages
telling everybody we're all one?

00:32:38.300 --> 00:32:40.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, that doesn't
do you any good

00:32:40.430 --> 00:32:42.790 align:middle line:90%
if you don't know it's true.

00:32:42.790 --> 00:32:46.390 align:middle line:90%
It's just a concept.

00:32:46.390 --> 00:32:48.460 align:middle line:90%
It's just a dogma.

00:32:48.460 --> 00:32:53.410 align:middle line:84%
But if you all of a
sudden actually understand

00:32:53.410 --> 00:32:55.300 align:middle line:90%
the mechanics on that--

00:32:55.300 --> 00:32:59.860 align:middle line:84%
is true, then actually
you start to integrate it.

00:32:59.860 --> 00:33:01.360 align:middle line:90%
You start to feel it.

00:33:01.360 --> 00:33:04.750 align:middle line:84%
And then you can build
technology based on that.

00:33:04.750 --> 00:33:08.290 align:middle line:84%
You can change the way you
run your world based on that.

00:33:08.290 --> 00:33:10.060 align:middle line:90%
That makes a huge difference.

00:33:10.060 --> 00:33:12.940 align:middle line:90%


00:33:12.940 --> 00:33:15.760 align:middle line:84%
So that's what
science does for us,

00:33:15.760 --> 00:33:22.420 align:middle line:84%
is that it removes the dogma,
it removes the beliefs,

00:33:22.420 --> 00:33:28.470 align:middle line:84%
meaning it replaces "I have to
have faith that, that is true."

00:33:28.470 --> 00:33:30.850 align:middle line:90%
It's like, Oh, we're all one.

00:33:30.850 --> 00:33:32.510 align:middle line:90%
Oh, well, I got to believe that.

00:33:32.510 --> 00:33:36.230 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't feel like it, but
I got to believe that.

00:33:36.230 --> 00:33:42.600 align:middle line:84%
To actually this is the proof
that this is how it works.

00:33:42.600 --> 00:33:45.510 align:middle line:84%
And this is the mechanics
on how it works.

00:33:45.510 --> 00:33:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And now I can start
to feel it in my body.

00:33:49.760 --> 00:33:54.440 align:middle line:84%
When I write these equations
and they show me this stuff,

00:33:54.440 --> 00:33:56.780 align:middle line:90%
it's very deep.

00:33:56.780 --> 00:34:02.690 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I can feel the
changes inside my being

00:34:02.690 --> 00:34:05.510 align:middle line:84%
that are occurring
as I'm integrating

00:34:05.510 --> 00:34:07.820 align:middle line:90%
when I'm discovering.

00:34:07.820 --> 00:34:13.010 align:middle line:10%
>> It sounds like this is what
you do that you get a thought

00:34:13.010 --> 00:34:14.120 align:middle line:10%
and intuition.

00:34:14.120 --> 00:34:16.880 align:middle line:10%
Would you like to talk
about maybe one or two

00:34:16.880 --> 00:34:18.170 align:middle line:10%
of your experiences with that?

00:34:18.170 --> 00:34:18.980 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:34:18.980 --> 00:34:26.060 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I think, first of all,
I don't believe in genius.

00:34:26.060 --> 00:34:28.940 align:middle line:10%
I believe everybody is genius.

00:34:28.940 --> 00:34:33.650 align:middle line:10%
It's like just the
fact that you're alive,

00:34:33.650 --> 00:34:37.040 align:middle line:10%
that you're made out of
100 trillion cells that

00:34:37.040 --> 00:34:39.440 align:middle line:10%
are operating just
perfectly, and you're

00:34:39.440 --> 00:34:43.100 align:middle line:10%
dividing a million cells a
second and billions of chemical

00:34:43.100 --> 00:34:46.520 align:middle line:10%
change are occurring every
second for you to stay alive,

00:34:46.520 --> 00:34:48.500 align:middle line:10%
that's all genius.

00:34:48.500 --> 00:34:52.159 align:middle line:10%
The miracle of your
existence is genius already,

00:34:52.159 --> 00:34:53.570 align:middle line:10%
like you were born genius.

00:34:53.570 --> 00:34:56.510 align:middle line:10%


00:34:56.510 --> 00:35:00.680 align:middle line:10%
And I think the only
difference between people

00:35:00.680 --> 00:35:06.020 align:middle line:10%
that are finding very new
solutions and creative ways

00:35:06.020 --> 00:35:14.660 align:middle line:10%
and that are very dynamic that
way is that they have a capacity

00:35:14.660 --> 00:35:24.810 align:middle line:10%
to focus on a specific problem
uninterrupted long enough

00:35:24.810 --> 00:35:28.230 align:middle line:10%
to get a really
good sense of it,

00:35:28.230 --> 00:35:34.320 align:middle line:10%
and start to pick on the
fringes of what's known,

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:37.590 align:middle line:10%
like feelings and intuition.

00:35:37.590 --> 00:35:41.110 align:middle line:10%
And so when people ask me, how
do you come up with this stuff?

00:35:41.110 --> 00:35:46.350 align:middle line:10%
This is literally it's like
thinking about something.

00:35:46.350 --> 00:35:47.640 align:middle line:10%
Thinking about reality.

00:35:47.640 --> 00:35:48.900 align:middle line:10%
Thinking about a problem.

00:35:48.900 --> 00:35:50.700 align:middle line:10%
Thinking about how things work.

00:35:50.700 --> 00:35:55.110 align:middle line:10%
And getting a sense
in my gut and my heart

00:35:55.110 --> 00:36:05.850 align:middle line:10%
and my being in my whole being
that it's like a certain way.

00:36:05.850 --> 00:36:16.400 align:middle line:10%
And that might sound very
unscientific to some.

00:36:16.400 --> 00:36:23.180 align:middle line:84%
But actually, this is how great
discoveries are made in science.

00:36:23.180 --> 00:36:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And then I start to see
these things in my head.

00:36:31.460 --> 00:36:35.090 align:middle line:84%
And I start asking more and
more questions about it.

00:36:35.090 --> 00:36:38.840 align:middle line:84%
And I start feeling more
and more answers about it.

00:36:38.840 --> 00:36:41.365 align:middle line:90%
I start seeing the whole thing.

00:36:41.365 --> 00:36:44.480 align:middle line:84%
I don't try to
extract the details

00:36:44.480 --> 00:36:48.760 align:middle line:90%
before I see the whole thing.

00:36:48.760 --> 00:36:52.310 align:middle line:84%
I try to remove any box
that I put around it.

00:36:52.310 --> 00:36:57.560 align:middle line:84%
I try to not isolate the
system, but open the system,

00:36:57.560 --> 00:36:59.180 align:middle line:90%
like, Oh, OK.

00:36:59.180 --> 00:37:03.350 align:middle line:10%
Well, if it's like this,
how is it in relationship

00:37:03.350 --> 00:37:05.010 align:middle line:10%
to the rest of the universe?

00:37:05.010 --> 00:37:08.840 align:middle line:84%
Why is it behaving this
way relative to the whole?

00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:09.640 align:middle line:90%
And so on.

00:37:09.640 --> 00:37:14.730 align:middle line:84%
And so then I get
a global sense.

00:37:14.730 --> 00:37:16.470 align:middle line:90%
I don't have details yet.

00:37:16.470 --> 00:37:19.590 align:middle line:84%
But I got an image,
I got a model,

00:37:19.590 --> 00:37:23.370 align:middle line:84%
I've got a global sense
of what it's doing.

00:37:23.370 --> 00:37:25.260 align:middle line:90%
And it's more than a thought.

00:37:25.260 --> 00:37:27.930 align:middle line:84%
It's a feeling of
how it's working.

00:37:27.930 --> 00:37:35.310 align:middle line:10%
And then I start to pick
apart pieces and start

00:37:35.310 --> 00:37:40.080 align:middle line:10%
to see OK, if they work in
the context of what's known

00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:43.440 align:middle line:10%
and what is known
and how would it

00:37:43.440 --> 00:37:47.320 align:middle line:10%
have to be modified
to match what I feel.

00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:49.890 align:middle line:10%
And so on.

00:37:49.890 --> 00:37:56.980 align:middle line:10%
And the result is
that eventually, you

00:37:56.980 --> 00:37:59.950 align:middle line:10%
may find that you have
to do some corrections

00:37:59.950 --> 00:38:06.700 align:middle line:10%
to your feelings, to
your initial model.

00:38:06.700 --> 00:38:12.880 align:middle line:10%
But in general, what I
found is that it naturally

00:38:12.880 --> 00:38:15.460 align:middle line:10%
tends towards the truth.

00:38:15.460 --> 00:38:18.650 align:middle line:10%
It naturally tends
towards the truth.

00:38:18.650 --> 00:38:23.320 align:middle line:10%
In fact, I think that
children naturally

00:38:23.320 --> 00:38:28.270 align:middle line:10%
tend towards the truth,
that they naturally

00:38:28.270 --> 00:38:33.610 align:middle line:10%
instinctively know what's up.

00:38:33.610 --> 00:38:36.580 align:middle line:10%
For instance, you
give a model that's

00:38:36.580 --> 00:38:43.060 align:middle line:10%
fairly arrested to a child
like the Big Bang model.

00:38:43.060 --> 00:38:47.950 align:middle line:10%
You say, it all started with
an explosion, a Big Bang.

00:38:47.950 --> 00:38:49.700 align:middle line:10%
And it made the universe.

00:38:49.700 --> 00:38:52.900 align:middle line:10%
It made all-- it made all space
and time, all the forces, all

00:38:52.900 --> 00:38:53.860 align:middle line:10%
the universe.

00:38:53.860 --> 00:38:57.590 align:middle line:10%
And the kid will look
at you typically.

00:38:57.590 --> 00:39:02.720 align:middle line:10%
And I have two children, I know,
with like some kind of dismayed

00:39:02.720 --> 00:39:03.980 align:middle line:10%
look in their face.

00:39:03.980 --> 00:39:08.060 align:middle line:10%
And they go, well,
what exploded?

00:39:08.060 --> 00:39:09.710 align:middle line:10%
What made it explode?

00:39:09.710 --> 00:39:10.880 align:middle line:10%
Why did it explode?

00:39:10.880 --> 00:39:13.400 align:middle line:10%
And what was it that exploded?

00:39:13.400 --> 00:39:15.620 align:middle line:10%
I mean, if it's
the whole universe,

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:18.500 align:middle line:10%
that means it was the
whole universe already.

00:39:18.500 --> 00:39:20.640 align:middle line:10%
So what happened before that?

00:39:20.640 --> 00:39:22.700 align:middle line:10%
And so like all these--

00:39:22.700 --> 00:39:27.080 align:middle line:10%
and naturally, so you
see the child naturally

00:39:27.080 --> 00:39:28.970 align:middle line:10%
is going to think
fractally, is going

00:39:28.970 --> 00:39:37.340 align:middle line:10%
to think that they must be
all kinds of things before.

00:39:37.340 --> 00:39:40.010 align:middle line:10%
It's not going to
say, well, I'm not

00:39:40.010 --> 00:39:43.130 align:middle line:10%
going to think about
what happened before.

00:39:43.130 --> 00:39:48.620 align:middle line:10%
I'm just going to assume
an explosion, which

00:39:48.620 --> 00:39:51.200 align:middle line:10%
is what we've done in physics.

00:39:51.200 --> 00:39:57.260 align:middle line:10%
Basically, we might as well
have changed the word God

00:39:57.260 --> 00:40:02.540 align:middle line:10%
for Big Bang, basically, because
we start the equation with, oh,

00:40:02.540 --> 00:40:05.060 align:middle line:10%
and there was a miracle.

00:40:05.060 --> 00:40:07.580 align:middle line:10%
And then da, da, da.

00:40:07.580 --> 00:40:10.700 align:middle line:10%
Well, that's not quite science.

00:40:10.700 --> 00:40:13.040 align:middle line:10%
That's not quite physics.

00:40:13.040 --> 00:40:21.800 align:middle line:84%
So naturally,
children will tend--

00:40:21.800 --> 00:40:25.670 align:middle line:84%
when we're young,
we're so creative.

00:40:25.670 --> 00:40:32.210 align:middle line:84%
And that's because we have
that sense that natural sense

00:40:32.210 --> 00:40:34.160 align:middle line:90%
of knowingness.

00:40:34.160 --> 00:40:40.520 align:middle line:84%
See knowingness doesn't
come from studying books.

00:40:40.520 --> 00:40:43.460 align:middle line:84%
Studying books and
studying what's known

00:40:43.460 --> 00:40:48.600 align:middle line:84%
is important because it might
give you ideas, first of all.

00:40:48.600 --> 00:40:51.690 align:middle line:84%
It might inspire
you, all this stuff.

00:40:51.690 --> 00:40:54.860 align:middle line:84%
But if you're going to do
something truly creative,

00:40:54.860 --> 00:40:58.890 align:middle line:84%
something truly transformative,
something truly new,

00:40:58.890 --> 00:41:01.610 align:middle line:84%
then you have to step
into the unknown.

00:41:01.610 --> 00:41:04.500 align:middle line:90%


00:41:04.500 --> 00:41:09.720 align:middle line:84%
And realize that
knowledge does not come--

00:41:09.720 --> 00:41:13.890 align:middle line:84%
like fundamental knowledge,
true knowledge, true creativity

00:41:13.890 --> 00:41:16.620 align:middle line:90%
does not come from the outside.

00:41:16.620 --> 00:41:20.670 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't come from
replicating what

00:41:20.670 --> 00:41:24.810 align:middle line:84%
you saw because then you're just
doing what everybody is doing.

00:41:24.810 --> 00:41:30.450 align:middle line:84%
And so it comes from
inside knowledge,

00:41:30.450 --> 00:41:33.340 align:middle line:84%
true knowledge
comes from within.

00:41:33.340 --> 00:41:36.150 align:middle line:84%
And what do we
know about within?

00:41:36.150 --> 00:41:40.860 align:middle line:84%
How much time in our
day do we spend actually

00:41:40.860 --> 00:41:43.530 align:middle line:90%
exploring what's within?

00:41:43.530 --> 00:41:46.020 align:middle line:84%
Are we connected to
what's within or are

00:41:46.020 --> 00:41:47.940 align:middle line:90%
we completely disconnected?

00:41:47.940 --> 00:41:53.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, clearly what's within
is doing an extremely good job

00:41:53.550 --> 00:41:58.790 align:middle line:84%
at keeping things going, like
your heart, your breathing,

00:41:58.790 --> 00:42:03.500 align:middle line:84%
your nervous system, millions
of chemical change every second,

00:42:03.500 --> 00:42:05.240 align:middle line:90%
it's running the show.

00:42:05.240 --> 00:42:09.140 align:middle line:90%
And it's got a long to do list.

00:42:09.140 --> 00:42:12.230 align:middle line:84%
Every second, it's
got a long to do list.

00:42:12.230 --> 00:42:16.550 align:middle line:84%
And if you had to
run that to do list,

00:42:16.550 --> 00:42:18.200 align:middle line:90%
it would not be a good day.

00:42:18.200 --> 00:42:22.220 align:middle line:84%
You would have a really
bad day really quick.

00:42:22.220 --> 00:42:28.100 align:middle line:84%
So there's something
