01:11:53.010 --> 01:11:57.330 align:middle line:90%
And I would classify people.

01:11:57.330 --> 01:12:01.350 align:middle line:84%
I could see strands
of people like,

01:12:01.350 --> 01:12:04.480 align:middle line:84%
oh, this is a person
that's more like this

01:12:04.480 --> 01:12:07.750 align:middle line:84%
and this is a person that's
more-- and I could see patterns.

01:12:07.750 --> 01:12:10.510 align:middle line:84%
And I would look in nature
and I would see patterns

01:12:10.510 --> 01:12:13.110 align:middle line:90%
and I would think--

01:12:13.110 --> 01:12:15.370 align:middle line:84%
and, I mean, there
was definitely a lot

01:12:15.370 --> 01:12:18.140 align:middle line:90%
of snow in Canada at the time.

01:12:18.140 --> 01:12:24.160 align:middle line:84%
And I would look at the
snowflakes and look at each one

01:12:24.160 --> 01:12:26.320 align:middle line:84%
and go, wow, they're
all different

01:12:26.320 --> 01:12:28.150 align:middle line:90%
but they're all hexagonal.

01:12:28.150 --> 01:12:31.090 align:middle line:84%
Like and why are
they all like this?

01:12:31.090 --> 01:12:34.890 align:middle line:90%
And what makes this happen?

01:12:34.890 --> 01:12:40.630 align:middle line:10%
And so I had an inquisitive
mind and I wanted to know.

01:12:40.630 --> 01:12:49.250 align:middle line:10%
And I felt like people were
as well living a double life.

01:12:49.250 --> 01:12:52.340 align:middle line:10%
I felt like there was
the part of people

01:12:52.340 --> 01:12:56.780 align:middle line:10%
that they were externalizing
like their behavior,

01:12:56.780 --> 01:13:00.590 align:middle line:10%
the way they are, but
then internally there

01:13:00.590 --> 01:13:03.650 align:middle line:10%
was a whole other person that--

01:13:03.650 --> 01:13:06.260 align:middle line:10%
asking much deeper questions.

01:13:06.260 --> 01:13:12.830 align:middle line:10%
And that person is
not often exposed.

01:13:12.830 --> 01:13:18.710 align:middle line:10%
And I would like, have very
deep philosophical conversation

01:13:18.710 --> 01:13:22.640 align:middle line:10%
with people trying to see
if I could help them expose

01:13:22.640 --> 01:13:26.420 align:middle line:10%
that deeper part
of themself that

01:13:26.420 --> 01:13:32.270 align:middle line:10%
is like asking deeper questions
about the nature of reality.

01:13:32.270 --> 01:13:34.100 align:middle line:10%
I had the--

01:13:34.100 --> 01:13:38.360 align:middle line:10%
I was fortunate that my father
was a child psychologist

01:13:38.360 --> 01:13:41.720 align:middle line:10%
and was a director
of child psychology

01:13:41.720 --> 01:13:43.310 align:middle line:10%
at the University of Montreal.

01:13:43.310 --> 01:13:48.560 align:middle line:10%
And so he was hanging out
with a lot of deep thinkers

01:13:48.560 --> 01:13:50.120 align:middle line:10%
and philosophers.

01:13:50.120 --> 01:13:52.130 align:middle line:10%
And my father used
to bring his students

01:13:52.130 --> 01:14:05.240 align:middle line:10%
to our home to have like group
psychology events, and so on.

01:14:05.240 --> 01:14:09.200 align:middle line:10%
And I would talk
with his student

01:14:09.200 --> 01:14:18.630 align:middle line:10%
and I just felt like
there's a mystery.

01:14:18.630 --> 01:14:25.020 align:middle line:10%
And I felt like if there's
a mystery and I'm here

01:14:25.020 --> 01:14:28.960 align:middle line:10%
and I know there's a mystery,
that means there's an answer.

01:14:28.960 --> 01:14:30.870 align:middle line:10%
It's not going to--

01:14:30.870 --> 01:14:34.800 align:middle line:10%
it can't be solved.

01:14:34.800 --> 01:14:38.370 align:middle line:84%
And often I was
told by many people

01:14:38.370 --> 01:14:41.680 align:middle line:84%
along the way,
many, many people,

01:14:41.680 --> 01:14:43.890 align:middle line:84%
you're never going to
solve that, you're never

01:14:43.890 --> 01:14:46.035 align:middle line:90%
going to know.

01:14:46.035 --> 01:14:50.520 align:middle line:84%
Just go along with it and forget
about it and just do your thing

01:14:50.520 --> 01:14:52.784 align:middle line:90%
and don't make waves.

01:14:52.784 --> 01:14:57.450 align:middle line:90%
And it was just not my type.

01:14:57.450 --> 01:14:59.550 align:middle line:90%
I just needed to know.

01:14:59.550 --> 01:15:05.970 align:middle line:84%
And I felt like
there is nothing--

01:15:05.970 --> 01:15:10.270 align:middle line:84%
if there's a question,
then there is an answer.

01:15:10.270 --> 01:15:17.660 align:middle line:84%
It's just a question of
actually feeling the answer,

01:15:17.660 --> 01:15:23.330 align:middle line:84%
knowing the answer,
experiencing the answer,

01:15:23.330 --> 01:15:28.190 align:middle line:84%
and then being able
to cognify that answer

01:15:28.190 --> 01:15:32.060 align:middle line:84%
at a deep enough level that
you can communicate it.

01:15:32.060 --> 01:15:36.290 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's in mathematics
or in conversation

01:15:36.290 --> 01:15:41.030 align:middle line:84%
or in philosophy, but to
be able to communicate it

01:15:41.030 --> 01:15:45.510 align:middle line:90%
and to explore it with others.

01:15:45.510 --> 01:15:53.390 align:middle line:84%
There is very
profound moments when

01:15:53.390 --> 01:15:57.770 align:middle line:84%
you're communicating
something that you believe

01:15:57.770 --> 01:16:05.000 align:middle line:84%
is a very deep truth with
others because typically others

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:06.785 align:middle line:90%
recognize it.

01:16:06.785 --> 01:16:10.850 align:middle line:84%
If they're just even just
a little bit open to it,

01:16:10.850 --> 01:16:15.260 align:middle line:84%
they will recognize it and
you will see that change

01:16:15.260 --> 01:16:17.130 align:middle line:90%
in the other person.

01:16:17.130 --> 01:16:20.520 align:middle line:84%
And they might
actually go further

01:16:20.520 --> 01:16:26.940 align:middle line:84%
than you did with that truth,
with that line of thought,

01:16:26.940 --> 01:16:29.380 align:middle line:90%
and you will learn as well.

01:16:29.380 --> 01:16:35.410 align:middle line:84%
And as you-- so it's really an
amazing collective evolution.

01:16:35.410 --> 01:16:38.130 align:middle line:90%


01:16:38.130 --> 01:16:49.020 align:middle line:84%
And it was very exciting
to have the possibility

01:16:49.020 --> 01:16:51.180 align:middle line:84%
to think about all
these things but I

01:16:51.180 --> 01:16:55.080 align:middle line:84%
was having a very hard time
in the educational system.

01:16:55.080 --> 01:17:00.030 align:middle line:10%
And my father being
a child psychologist

01:17:00.030 --> 01:17:07.260 align:middle line:10%
and involved in
education and so on, I

01:17:07.260 --> 01:17:11.040 align:middle line:10%
was probably his worst
case, his worst nightmare.

01:17:11.040 --> 01:17:15.700 align:middle line:10%
But I was just a child
that didn't fit anywhere.

01:17:15.700 --> 01:17:21.730 align:middle line:10%
And so early on I had to
go and do my own thing.

01:17:21.730 --> 01:17:26.070 align:middle line:10%
And I spent many, many
years, some 25 years

01:17:26.070 --> 01:17:29.190 align:middle line:10%
in nature in the
mountains climbing,

01:17:29.190 --> 01:17:35.710 align:middle line:10%
skiing, and so on because I
wanted to be close to nature.

01:17:35.710 --> 01:17:41.760 align:middle line:10%
And that was really important to
me, to feel the natural world.

01:17:41.760 --> 01:17:45.630 align:middle line:10%
Maybe if I could feel
the natural world enough,

01:17:45.630 --> 01:17:48.990 align:middle line:10%
it would tell me something,
it would talk to me,

01:17:48.990 --> 01:17:50.520 align:middle line:10%
it would tell--

01:17:50.520 --> 01:17:54.270 align:middle line:10%
I could become
more empathic to it

01:17:54.270 --> 01:17:59.110 align:middle line:10%
and I could understand its
nature at a deeper level.

01:17:59.110 --> 01:18:04.380 align:middle line:10%
And so I loved being in nature.

01:18:04.380 --> 01:18:17.950 align:middle line:10%
And eventually I had to
become more than just

01:18:17.950 --> 01:18:21.070 align:middle line:10%
internally thinking about this.

01:18:21.070 --> 01:18:26.530 align:middle line:10%
I knew that I had to
explore it more in detail

01:18:26.530 --> 01:18:30.290 align:middle line:10%
and formalize it
and transmit it.

01:18:30.290 --> 01:18:37.720 align:middle line:10%
And so I started on this
daunting path of learning

01:18:37.720 --> 01:18:40.300 align:middle line:10%
physics and
mathematics and so on

01:18:40.300 --> 01:18:46.360 align:middle line:10%
to eventually write these
equations that describe,

01:18:46.360 --> 01:18:49.495 align:middle line:10%
I think, the fundamental
nature of reality.

01:18:49.495 --> 01:18:52.738 align:middle line:90%


01:18:52.738 --> 01:18:55.350 align:middle line:10%
>> OK, I feel like we
skipped over a lot.

01:18:55.350 --> 01:18:56.150 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHS]

01:18:56.150 --> 01:18:59.565 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah, sorry.

01:18:59.565 --> 01:19:00.365 align:middle line:10%
>> There it is.

01:19:00.365 --> 01:19:03.230 align:middle line:10%
>> You're going to have
to do a lot of cutting.

01:19:03.230 --> 01:19:06.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Oh, no.

01:19:06.270 --> 01:19:07.070 align:middle line:10%
It was beautiful.

01:19:07.070 --> 01:19:09.212 align:middle line:10%
So I want to make sure that
you have an opportunity

01:19:09.212 --> 01:19:11.170 align:middle line:10%
to say something that
you feel needs to be said

01:19:11.170 --> 01:19:13.940 align:middle line:10%
and I'm not asking,
or something that you

01:19:13.940 --> 01:19:15.680 align:middle line:10%
feel is important to say.

01:19:15.680 --> 01:19:17.420 align:middle line:90%
>> I appreciate it.

01:19:17.420 --> 01:19:19.460 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, thank you.

01:19:19.460 --> 01:19:24.440 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, I think
what's important at this time

01:19:24.440 --> 01:19:29.730 align:middle line:84%
is that people
realize that there

01:19:29.730 --> 01:19:36.048 align:middle line:84%
is more to reality than
what it appears to be.

01:19:36.048 --> 01:19:43.170 align:middle line:84%
That there's many-- from
traditions that talk about

01:19:43.170 --> 01:19:47.690 align:middle line:84%
it's all an illusion,
what about--

01:19:47.690 --> 01:19:53.670 align:middle line:84%
and in one sense I
think that's accurate

01:19:53.670 --> 01:19:58.360 align:middle line:84%
as much as the reverse
statement is accurate,

01:19:58.360 --> 01:20:01.980 align:middle line:90%
which is everything is real.

01:20:01.980 --> 01:20:04.860 align:middle line:84%
What I mean by
everything is real is

01:20:04.860 --> 01:20:13.350 align:middle line:84%
that your thoughts, your
feelings, your intuition, it's

01:20:13.350 --> 01:20:14.500 align:middle line:90%
all real.

01:20:14.500 --> 01:20:18.570 align:middle line:84%
It's not something
that's just some kind

01:20:18.570 --> 01:20:21.210 align:middle line:84%
of like random
chemical event that's

01:20:21.210 --> 01:20:24.060 align:middle line:84%
occurring in your brain
that's making that happen,

01:20:24.060 --> 01:20:29.500 align:middle line:84%
like there's something that
the universe is talking to you

01:20:29.500 --> 01:20:32.290 align:middle line:90%
and you're talking back.

01:20:32.290 --> 01:20:37.240 align:middle line:84%
And you don't know you're in a
conversation with the universe,

01:20:37.240 --> 01:20:42.550 align:middle line:84%
although you might realize it
in your being, in your head.

01:20:42.550 --> 01:20:44.880 align:middle line:84%
Like you might
say-- you might know

01:20:44.880 --> 01:20:49.180 align:middle line:84%
because we do have these
conversations constantly

01:20:49.180 --> 01:20:52.760 align:middle line:90%
in the shower, going to work.

01:20:52.760 --> 01:20:55.870 align:middle line:84%
It's not like we're sitting
there completely blank.

01:20:55.870 --> 01:20:59.690 align:middle line:84%
So we're driving and we're
thinking about 20 million things

01:20:59.690 --> 01:21:03.220 align:middle line:84%
and we're having a
conversation about them,

01:21:03.220 --> 01:21:05.150 align:middle line:90%
who are we talking about?

01:21:05.150 --> 01:21:07.480 align:middle line:90%
Who are we talking to?

01:21:07.480 --> 01:21:09.520 align:middle line:90%
What is going on?

01:21:09.520 --> 01:21:15.220 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're talking to
this fundamental field.

01:21:15.220 --> 01:21:19.570 align:middle line:84%
We're part of this
fundamental field.

01:21:19.570 --> 01:21:26.080 align:middle line:84%
And we're like a tool of this
fundamental field learning

01:21:26.080 --> 01:21:31.680 align:middle line:84%
about itself, growing,
evolving, transforming.

01:21:31.680 --> 01:21:34.440 align:middle line:84%
And we're all connected
through that field.

01:21:34.440 --> 01:21:40.164 align:middle line:10%
We all have the same faith,
we're all on the same planet.

01:21:40.164 --> 01:21:43.240 align:middle line:10%
Everything we do in a day.

01:21:43.240 --> 01:21:45.450 align:middle line:10%
So to have like--

01:21:45.450 --> 01:21:46.890 align:middle line:10%
level of awareness.

01:21:46.890 --> 01:21:48.330 align:middle line:10%
What am I doing?

01:21:48.330 --> 01:21:50.460 align:middle line:10%
What is the actions I'm taking?

01:21:50.460 --> 01:21:53.010 align:middle line:10%
What am I thinking?

01:21:53.010 --> 01:21:56.760 align:middle line:10%
Right now there's all these
manifestations and riots

01:21:56.760 --> 01:22:02.740 align:middle line:10%
about racism and
so on in the world.

01:22:02.740 --> 01:22:14.140 align:middle line:10%
And it's like many people that
nobody would consider racist,

01:22:14.140 --> 01:22:16.810 align:middle line:10%
does that mean they don't
have those thoughts?

01:22:16.810 --> 01:22:20.340 align:middle line:10%
No, it doesn't actually.

01:22:20.340 --> 01:22:25.350 align:middle line:10%
If you did good accounting
of your thoughts and you--

01:22:25.350 --> 01:22:30.550 align:middle line:10%
you will find that sometimes
those thoughts come up.

01:22:30.550 --> 01:22:31.990 align:middle line:10%
Where are they coming from?

01:22:31.990 --> 01:22:39.810 align:middle line:10%
And it might be the Chinese
or the Africans or--

01:22:39.810 --> 01:22:48.570 align:middle line:10%
but it's like--
and it's happening.

01:22:48.570 --> 01:22:51.770 align:middle line:10%
And if you're not aware
that it's happening,

01:22:51.770 --> 01:22:54.560 align:middle line:10%
then there's no way
for you to edit it.

01:22:54.560 --> 01:22:56.420 align:middle line:10%
There's no way for
you to transform it.

01:22:56.420 --> 01:23:01.160 align:middle line:10%
And now you're part of something
you don't want to be part of.

01:23:01.160 --> 01:23:09.920 align:middle line:10%
So to actually become aware, to
have self awareness to the point

01:23:09.920 --> 01:23:13.670 align:middle line:10%
that you're able
to actually monitor

01:23:13.670 --> 01:23:17.300 align:middle line:10%
what is the conversation
that's going on here?

01:23:17.300 --> 01:23:19.700 align:middle line:10%
And who am I talking to?

01:23:19.700 --> 01:23:25.070 align:middle line:10%
And to realize you're talking to
a field, a morphogenetic field

01:23:25.070 --> 01:23:27.830 align:middle line:10%
that connects all
things, and that you

01:23:27.830 --> 01:23:30.830 align:middle line:10%
have a responsibility
in what you're

01:23:30.830 --> 01:23:36.290 align:middle line:10%
putting in that field, how
you're interpreting reality

01:23:36.290 --> 01:23:41.720 align:middle line:10%
is impacting the whole, then
you realize your responsibility.

01:23:41.720 --> 01:23:45.440 align:middle line:10%
And you're going to fail,
you're going to get pissed off,

01:23:45.440 --> 01:23:48.638 align:middle line:10%
you're going to scream,
you're going to have moments.

01:23:48.638 --> 01:23:50.430 align:middle line:10%
Somebody's going to
cut you on the highway,

01:23:50.430 --> 01:23:54.000 align:middle line:10%
you're going to give
them the finger, it's OK.

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:55.500 align:middle line:10%
It's OK.

01:23:55.500 --> 01:23:59.610 align:middle line:10%
Like, you have to
be good to yourself,

01:23:59.610 --> 01:24:04.290 align:middle line:10%
to understand you will have
hard times, you will fail,

01:24:04.290 --> 01:24:05.850 align:middle line:10%
you will do the wrong thing.

01:24:05.850 --> 01:24:12.120 align:middle line:10%
What's important is how fast
can you go back to being benign,

01:24:12.120 --> 01:24:16.200 align:middle line:10%
to learning from what
happened, to evolving.

01:24:16.200 --> 01:24:18.460 align:middle line:10%
That is what's important.

01:24:18.460 --> 01:24:22.020 align:middle line:10%
It's the universe
helping evolve you?

01:24:22.020 --> 01:24:23.700 align:middle line:10%
Take the opportunity.

01:24:23.700 --> 01:24:29.550 align:middle line:10%
Whatever is happening that may
be looking negative in your life

01:24:29.550 --> 01:24:31.780 align:middle line:10%
is an opportunity for growth.

01:24:31.780 --> 01:24:35.250 align:middle line:10%
And if you take it
like that, then you

01:24:35.250 --> 01:24:42.870 align:middle line:10%
will be the most brilliant and
the most amazing contributor

01:24:42.870 --> 01:24:46.220 align:middle line:10%
to the human experience.

01:24:46.220 --> 01:24:48.000 align:middle line:90%